  "outlook": "India's growth premium faces a breve termine compression from the shock petrolifero. If Hormuz remains closed for more than 2-4 weeks, inflation could exceed 5% and force RBI to pause normalizzazione dei tassi. Fiscal impact of fuel subsidies could add 0.5-0.8% of GDP to the deficit. India's non-alignment diplomacy allows it to potentially source discounted Russian oil, providing partial offset. The a medio termine structural growth story (demographics, digital infrastructure, manifatturiero shift) rimane intatto.",
  "investor_implications": "Sovrappesare Indian IT services (USD earners, energy-agnostic) and sottopesare ad alta intensita energetica industrials. INR hedge recommended given pressione al deprezzamento. Indian government bonds face yield pressure on inflation and fiscal concerns. Monitorare RBI statements for any emergency rate action. India remains a structural sovrappesare but tactical caution warranted.",
  "active_alerts": [
